1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:09,665
Now here is where it gets spicy,  a topic is a named, durable, ordered log of records — conceptually similar to a database table, but append-only and replayable.

2
00:00:09,615 --> 00:00:13,096
Every topic is divided into one or more partitions.

3
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:17,509
A partition is the fundamental unit of parallelism and ordering in Kafka.

